  "stem": "<p>The functions f and g are defined as f(x) = (1/5)x - 8 and g(x) = (4/5)x + 23. If the function h is defined as h(x) = f(x) + g(x), what is the x-coordinate of the x-intercept of the graph of y = h(x) in the xy-plane?</p>",
  "answerOptions": null,
  "keys": [
    "-15"
  ],
  "rationale": "<p>h(x) = (1/5)x - 8 + (4/5)x + 23 = x + 15. Setting h(x) = 0: x + 15 = 0, so x = -15.</p>",
